headline: IBM, Cisco Team Up For Quantum Computing Network Plan. IBM Stock Gains Above Key Level.
summary: IBM will partner with Cisco Systems to build a network of "large-scale, fault-tolerant quantum computers" by early next decade, the companies announced Thursday.  Both IBM stock and Cisco shares were higher as Nvidia's earnings report lifted tech stocks more broadly.  The Dow Jones giants will collaborate on what IBM called networked distributed quantum computing, allowing powerful quantum computers to work together to run computations over a massive scale.

content.title: IBM, Cisco Team Up For Quantum Computing Network Plan. IBM Stock Gains Above Key Level.
content.summary: IBM will partner with Cisco Systems to build a network of "large-scale, fault-tolerant quantum computers" by early next decade, the companies announced Thursday.  Both IBM stock and Cisco shares were higher as Nvidia's earnings report lifted tech stocks more broadly.  The Dow Jones giants will collaborate on what IBM called networked distributed quantum computing, allowing powerful quantum computers to work together to run computations over a massive scale.

headline: Spencer Jakab | Will Newer Bitcoin Owners Hold On?
summary: Bitcoin has a lot more leverage and complexity behind it than a share of IBM, though.  Ordinary savers with no desire to carry a chunk of their net worth around on an encrypted thumb drive have embraced cheap, convenient exchange-traded funds like the iShares Bitcoin Trust (IBIT).  More gullible ones piled into bitcoin treasury companies like Strategy that long fetched a premium to their holdings.

headline: Cisco & IBM's quantum internet, mortgage rates tick higher
summary: Yahoo Finance anchor Julie Hyman tracks Thursday's top moving stocks and biggest market stories in this Market Minute. Bitcoin (BTC-USD) is extending recent declines, now under the $88,000 mark. Mortgage rates are ticking higher this week, with the 30-year fixed rate at 6.26% — up from 6.24% last week, according to data from Freddie Mac (FMCC). Cisco (CSCO) and IBM (IBM) are partnering on a project that the companies say could lead to "quantum internet." Stay up to date on the latest market action, minute-by-minute, with Yahoo Finance's Market Minute.
